## Search for Events

> **1. Get the Root resource:**

<%= curl('GET', 'https://api.viagogo.net/v2') %>

~~~ csharp
var api = new ViagogoClient("clientId",
                            "clientSecret",
                            new ProductHeaderValue("MyAwesomeApp"));
var root = await api.Root.GetAsync();
~~~

> **2. Search for the Team/Artist/Tournament/etc Category:**

<%= curl('GET', ROOT['_links']['viagogo:search']['href']) %>

~~~ csharp
var searchResults = await api.Search.GetAllAsync("one direction");
~~~

<%= json_paged_resource(:search_result, "viagogo:search") %>

> **3. Get the Details of the Category**

<%= curl('GET', SEARCH_RESULT['_links']['searchresult:category']['href']) %>

~~~ csharp
var category = await api.Categories.GetAsync(searchResults[0].Id);
~~~

> **4. Page through the Events in the Category**

<%= curl('GET', CATEGORY_PERFORMER['_links']['category:events']['href']) %>

~~~ csharp
var events = await api.Events.GetAllByCategoryAsync(category.Id);
~~~

API v2 provides access to the same search features available on the viagogo website. Your application can use this search to quickly find a particular category, event, venue or metro area.

### 1. Start at the Root

As is the case when retrieving most data in API v2, you should start by getting the [`Root`](#root) resource to find the hyperlink to the resource you care about.

### 2. Search for the Team/Artist/Tournament/etc Category

Follow the [`viagogo:search`](#viagogosearch) link to query for entities you are interested in.

### 3. Get the Details of the Category

[`SearchResult`](#searchresult) resources only contain very basic entity information so you should follow the link on the result that will get you more information about the entity (see [`searchresult:category`](#searchresultcategory), [`searchresult:event`](#searchresultevent), [`searchresult:metroarea`](#searchresultmetroarea) and [`searchresult:venue`](#searchresultvenue))

### 4. Page through the Events in the Category

Follow the [`category:events`](#categoryevents) link to get the first page of events under the category. Once we have the first page, we can follow the `next` links to retrieve all pages (see [pagination](#pagination)).